        "fs-heading": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "It started with one bathroom.",
            "size": "3xl"
          }
        },
        "fs-text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Dan Kovac spent twelve years as a finish carpenter before a neighbor asked him to redo a bathroom in 2004. He ran that job the way he'd always wished the companies he worked for ran theirs: a real price up front, a swept floor every night, and a call the moment anything changed.</p><p>Three hundred and forty projects later, that's still the whole business model. Bedrock stays small on purpose — few enough jobs at once that Dan still walks every site, every week.</p>",
            "size": "base",
            "uppercase": false,
            "muted": false
          }
        }
      },
      "blocksOrder": ["fs-eyebrow", "fs-heading", "fs-text"]
    },
